<br>
Those SoT who left during this most recent bullshit fest are the ones taking the road less travelled by.  It took a thread of 294 posts to drag the SOT leadership kicking and screaming to the apology - don't offer it now as responsible &quot;taking ownership of one's mistakes&quot;.  This is not an isolated incident.  This was just the most public of many actions SOT has taken in the past year.  For once, the SoT PR machine failed, and you all @#%$ up in such a public way that your usual habit of trying to get everyone to bury their head in the sand didn't work.  I won't even bother listing all the times you have pulled this kind of bullshit.<br>
<br>
You want proof?  Read Thundaron's first post on this matter.  Read Dwallyn's posted logs - this is the essence of SoT most of us have thought existed but hoped was not true.  This is the essence of what everyone is told to &quot;take the SOT bandwagon&quot; bashing with a grain of salt.  Well, you can take your salt back, we don't need it. <br>
<br>
There was a time when SoT and NB were almost sister guilds.  I xped with and raided with SoT countless times in HS, VS raids, Dragon killings, Kedge, planar raids - all with Karadoc, Lazreth, Femke, Rana, Nycah, Thundaron, Cassidy, Shane, Clerise, Pacemaker, etc etc.  Then the decision to become Uber happened around the time SoT first started going for Trak.  The attitude changed, and the lack of respect for everyone else on the server started.  Well, I hope you're happy with how uber you've become, and I hope its worth the pariah status you are now enjoying.<br>
<br>
This isn't a one off mistake SoT made, but a culmination of all they have worked for, and how they treat almost everyone they encounter.  This time, it just happened in such a public venue, with enough witnesses it couldn't be hidden or dismissed.<br>
<br>
Standing by and defending your guild during a &quot;trying time&quot; is commendable.  Supporting one where the leadership is corrupt and incapable of common decency is not.  I would turn you to the AA prayer Malidar:<br>
<br>
God grant me the serenity to accept the things I cannot change,<br>
<br>
the Courage to change the things I can,<br>
<br>
And the wisdom to know the difference.<br>
<br>
<br>
Dwallyn, Galudina and Pahraith had that wisdom, and exercised their courage.  You have your serenity.  I think they are the better off.<br>
